---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service | Prestige, Inc." description="Terms of Service for Prestige, Inc. website and SMS communications.">
	<section class="bg-white py-20 text-brand-slate">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-10">
			<p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand-blue">Legal</p>
			<h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-navy">Terms of Service</h1>
			<p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: May 18, 2026</p>

			<div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-base leading-8 text-slate-700">
				<section aria-labelledby="terms-acceptance">
					<h2 id="terms-acceptance" class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Acceptance of Terms</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						By accessing this website, submitting a quote request, or communicating with Prestige, Inc., you agree to these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, do not use this website or submit information through our forms.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="terms-services">
					<h2 id="terms-services" class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Transportation Requests</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						Information submitted through this website is used to evaluate and respond to transportation and logistics inquiries. A submitted form does not create a binding shipment contract, rate confirmation, carrier agreement, or guarantee of service availability. Final shipment terms must be confirmed in writing by authorized representatives.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="terms-user-responsibilities">
					<h2 id="terms-user-responsibilities" class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">User Responsibilities</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information when requesting a quote or communicating about a shipment. You are responsible for ensuring that submitted freight details, contact information, pickup and delivery requirements, and special handling instructions are accurate.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="terms-sms">
					<h2 id="terms-sms" class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">SMS Terms</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						By opting in to SMS communications, you authorize Prestige, Inc. to send text messages related to your quote request, shipment inquiry, scheduling, service coordination, and customer support. Message frequency varies based on your request, shipment status, and communication needs.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-3">
						Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages. Delivery depends on your mobile carrier, device, network availability, and other factors outside the control of Prestige, Inc.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-3 rounded-2xl border border-brand-safety/40 bg-amber-50 p-5 font-semibold text-brand-slate">
						Reply STOP to cancel, HELP for help. Message and data rates may apply.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="terms-limitations">
					<h2 id="terms-limitations" class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Limitation of Liability</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						To the fullest extent permitted by law, Prestige, Inc. is not responsible for indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or punitive damages arising from website use, quote submissions, or communication delays. Any transportation-specific liability is governed by the applicable written agreement, bill of lading, tariff, or governing law.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="terms-updates">
					<h2 id="terms-updates" class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Updates</h2>
					<p class="mt-3">
						Prestige, Inc. may update these Terms of Service from time to time. Continued use of the website after updates are posted means you accept the revised terms.
					</p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>